Privacy Policy for Admins and Reporters Panel App

Last Updated: 13-09-2023]

This Privacy Policy outlines the practices and procedures governing the collection, use, and protection of personal information by the Admins and Reporters Panel App ("PL-Admin") developed for use with Publicline ("the News App"). The News App and the App collectively are referred to as "our services."

By using the App, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Privacy Policy. Please read this document carefully.

Information We Collect
User Account Information: To use the App, you may be required to create an account, which includes providing your name, email address, username, and password.

User Generated Content: We may collect information you provide while using the App, including text, images, and other content you submit.

Usage Information: We collect information about how you use the App, such as log data, device information (including device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers), and usage statistics.

How We Use Your Information
Account Management: We use your account information to provide and manage your access to the App, including user authentication, account recovery, and communication related to your account.

User Content: User-generated content may be published, displayed, or shared within the App for the purpose of managing and enhancing the News App's content.

Usage Analytics: We may use usage information for analytics purposes to improve the App's functionality and user experience.

Data Sharing
We do not share your personal information with third parties except in the following circumstances:

With Your Consent: We may share your information with third parties when you provide explicit consent to do so.

Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information if required by law, legal process, or in response to a valid government request.

Service Providers: We may engage third-party service providers to assist with app development, maintenance, or hosting. These service providers may have access to your information but are bound by confidentiality agreements.

Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission or storage can be guaranteed as completely secure. You acknowledge the inherent security risks of sharing information online and accept these risks.

Data Retention
We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.

Your Rights
You have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:

Access and Correction: You may request access to and correction of your personal information.
Data Portability: You may request a copy of your data in a structured, machine-readable format.
Deletion: You may request the deletion of your account and associated data.
Withdrawal of Consent: You can withdraw your consent to our processing of your information at any time.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or for legal reasons. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated policy within the App.

Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at nammaoorseithi@gmail.com .

By using the App, you consent to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App.

